snippet.textDisplay: 2:26 whether or not he heard the song while he was alive....he's using copyrighted material. Those melodies are nearly identical and it is copyrighted as Yellowcards melody for....whatever the song was called. I did not ever like Yellowcard so the title honestly didn't stick for me. But, again, they wrote a song using that melody, that song is copyrighted and Juice Curls or whatever wrote a song with a nearly identical melody. He made money on an already copyrighted property that he didn't own. It sucks, and the outcome isn't guaranteed, but if Yellowcard wins I don't think will be a difficult defense for them to prove. You admitted the melodies are strikingly similar, but its sooooo simple that.....well, that's not the question. Doesn't Death Cab for Cutie have an album called "You Can Play These Songs With Chords" and they're all like 4-6 chords per song and basic as fuck? If not DCFC then some shitty band does. But just because they're simple doesn't mean the copyrights don't hold up. Also, unfortunately, it is not uncommon for professional artists to write a song to a public domain melody and then copyright their song thus removing that melody from the public domain and making it private property of an artist that didn't actually compose the music, or that artist's record company.

my thoughts about your vid.
1. yes, yellowcards song isnt similar enough to juice wrlds. this lawsuit isnt justified. but if it was justified:

snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Drew! I'm hoping I'm not too late to suggest a charity for your video.

I know you're removed from this but I'm Australian and currently we're experiencing terrible wild fires that have been burning for months. As of now, more land has burned than the whole country of Denmark and The Netherlands. It's an ecological disaster, with nearly half a billion animals being killed. People have also died and many homes and properties have been lost.

My family is preparing to evacuate from our home, a place that has never before been affected by fires like this.

There are lots of excellent charities and organisations that are doing great things, so I've left a link where you can look at all of them.
Some, like the red cross, are assisting people who need help finding shelter and need supplies after losing their houses. Others, like the RSPCA, are helping animals. There's also links to support the fire brigade services in the affected areas, which often have a high number of volunteers.

https://www.google.com/amp/s/amp.news.com.au/technology/environment/bushfire-relief-how-you-can-help-those-in-need/news-story/a0476ac3538b8c373f281ea6be204421

I've loved your work for a long time and I look forward to your videos every time. Thanks for being an awesome creator, and please consider one or more of these charities. Thank you x

Her brother has been in the hospital and was just diagnosed with GBS (Guillain-Barre Syndrome).
